casebody.data:
FRANK C. ROBEY, Clerk, v. CARL MANTELL [No. 69,

April Term, 1938.]

Decided August 3rd, 1938. The cause' was argued before Bond, C. J., URNER,. Offutt, Parke, Sloan, Mitchell, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ. Hilary W. Gans, Deputy Attorney General, with whom was Herbert R. O’Conor, Attorney General, on the brief, for the appellant. Daniel Ellison and Ernest F. Fadum, for the appellee. Bond, C. J.,

delivered the opinion of the Court.
